The alt text on a linked image is used to describe the link destination. Links should be brief, clear and concise, as screen reader users often listen to the list of links on the page to find content of interest. Long alternative text inside a link often indicates that the image's text alternative is describing the image instead rather than the link.

I promise to continue that fight in Washington if I’m re-elected. - Angus #MentalHealth #Support #COVID19 #Maine #Students #SupportOurKids #Caribou #Houlton #PresqueIsle #Westbrook #Biddeford"

Today and every day we are indebted to those 2,977 lives that were cut short, including 6 Maine residents, 343 firefighters, and 72 law enforcement officers. Let’s also remind ourselves of the values that unite us—freedom of religion, the right to individual expression, and equal justice under the law. It’s our duty to uphold these principles, just as those who came before us did, even at the highest cost. - Angus #September11 #NeverForget #Maine #FirstResponders"

From there, he shifted his focus to causes that would better the lives of people in Maine. He served as your Governor, and in January 2013, he was sworn in to serve as your United States Senator. Today, he lives in Brunswick with his wife, Mary. They have one daughter, Molly, and four sons, Angus III, Duncan, James and Ben, along with seven precious grandchildren.

altLongLinked.what: Linked img alt value longer than 160 characters

texts:
The alt text on a linked image is used to describe the link destination. Links should be brief, clear and concise, as screen reader users often listen to the list of links on the page to find content of interest. Long alternative text inside a link often indicates that the image's text alternative is describing the image instead rather than the link.

It won’t be too long until the leaves start to change! Good luck everyone, and remember, no matter how ridiculous you look, stay warm! - Angus #FridayNightLights 🏈 #Maine #Saco #Brunswick"
